104
00:16:07,407 --> 00:16:08,309
SECOND CULT.

105
00:16:08,950 --> 00:16:22,429
To the native Indian of Peru, the continual sight of the snow-hoarded Andes conveys naught of dread, except, perhaps, in the mere fancying of the eternal frosted desolateness reigning at such vast altitudes,

106
00:16:22,409 --> 00:16:29,158
and the natural conceit of what a fearfulness it would be to lose oneself in such inhuman solitudes.

107
00:16:29,338 --> 00:16:43,996
Much the same is it with the back woodsmen of the West, who, with comparative indifference, views an unbounded prairie sheeted with driven snow, no shadow of tree or twig to break the fixed trance of whiteness.

108
00:16:44,297 --> 00:16:51,606
Not so the sailor, beholding the scenery of the Antarctic seas, were at times, by some infernal trick,

109
00:16:51,586 --> 00:16:54,551
Of legerdemain in the powers of frost and air.

110
00:16:55,112 --> 00:17:09,595
He, shivering and half shipwrecked, Instead of rainbows speaking hope and solace To his misery, views what seems a boundless churchyard Grinning upon him, with its lean ice monuments And splintered crosses.

111
00:17:09,575 --> 00:17:17,587
But thou say'st, methinks that, white blood chapter about whiteness is but a white flag hung out from a craven soul.

112
00:17:18,328 --> 00:17:20,852
Thou surrender'st to a hypo, Ishmael.

113
00:17:20,932 --> 00:17:26,200
Tell me, why this strong young colt fold in some peaceful valley of Vermont?

114
00:17:26,180 --> 00:17:46,922
Far removed from all beasts of prey, why is it, that upon the sunniest day, if you but shake a fresh buffalo-robe behind him, so that he cannot even see it, but only smells its wild animal, muskiness why, will he start, snort, and with bursting eyes paw the ground in frenzies of a fright?

115
00:17:46,902 --> 00:18:00,945
